message.content:
cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel approach to improve the quality of class conditional image generation and super-resolution using GANs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new discriminator that incorporates conditional information in a different way than previous frameworks, which is related to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses parametric functional transformation of conditional batch normalization layers in the generator, which is related to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image datasets and produces high-quality images, which is related to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper extends the application to super-resolution, which is related to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
